  <content:encoded xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><![CDATA[<p>I was reading <a href="http://hyperthink.net/blog/">Steve's</a> blog with my browser earlier today when I noticed his odd permalink url's. Instead of a url like "http://devhawk.net/PermaLink.aspx?guid=9abbd5ea-3a10-44d8-8872-877033b7349c", his look like "http://hyperthink.net/blog/PermaLink,guid,fc99ce5e-b748-44f0-853d-0a261632b885.aspx". Turns out it's a standard feature of dasBlog! Just check "Enable URL rewriting" in the config page and you're set. Now my permalink url's look like Steve's. </p><p>Since Google doesn't index pages based on query string, this feature should make my site more easily crawled and googled.</p><p>Update: This feature breaks sub category specific feeds, like "<a href="CategoryView.aspx?category=Blogging%7CdasBlog">Blogging | dasBlog</a>", so I'm turning it back off until someone can fix the bug.</p>]]></content:encoded>
